snippet.textDisplay:
Wow... actually teared up at the youtube angels part. I think this is a really good representation of youtube until now and the perfect time for it too. It's about to be 2020, the end of a decade, so a larger overall rewind feels right. If youtube doesn't take a hint and do something like this next year with the creators, how rewind used to be, I'll be more then disappointed.


The only thing I actually really really appreciated about this year's rewind despite the almost complete lack of effort was the inclusion of much much smaller creators, and a good number of international creators as well. That's the one thing I think was smart and should be appreciated. There should have been more effort though. How about flying them out to be a part of rewind in real life like usual, or at least having them record something from home to be included. LOL I guess that would be too much to ask though.


Any ways man, amazing work. It's unbelievable what amazing work one person (or even a very small team if that's what you've got going on) can do, significantly better than an entire corporation with unlimited resources.
